cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with text generation using GANs. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as GANs are a popular machine learning technique. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as GANs are a subset of AI. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as GANs use neural networks. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as GANs have been used for image generation and the paper proposes a method for text generation using word embeddings, which are also used in computer vision tasks.
